Leadership Team



Board of Directors



Committee Charters







Corporate Governance
Working in one of the world’s most highly regulated industries, Arlington Asset Investment Corp. strives for full compliance, in both letter and spirit, with all of the laws and regulations governing our securities industry businesses.
We firmly believe that our commitment to ethical practices and compliance is vital to our long-term success and to our mission of maximizing the value of the company for shareholders.
We have clear policies regarding business ethics, insider trading, confidential and proprietary information, investor relations, equal opportunity, sexual harassment, substance abuse and other vital workplace issues. All of our employees are made aware of our policies and are issued an employee handbook that outlines them. To ensure appropriate conduct, employees have access to training and supervisor review.
Arlington Asset operates under a Statement of Business Principles that provides further guidance regarding our corporate commitment to legal, ethical and respectful conduct.
From this page you may access charters for the Arlington Asset's Board of Director's Audit, Compensation, Nominating and Governance committees and our Statement of Business Principles, Corporate Governance Guidelines and Bylaws.

